  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until it's translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for another minute.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, turmeric, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the rinsed red lentils and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the pitted prunes, chopped onion mixture, water, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 25 minutes, or until the lentils are tender.",
    "Stir in some water if the stew becomes too thick.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot over injera bread or with some rice."
